---
import GuideLayout from "../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";

const title = "Secrets Manager pricing: what to model (secrets + API calls)";
const description =
  "A practical Secrets Manager pricing checklist: secret-month baseline plus API request charges, and the common patterns that create request-driven cost spikes.";
---
<GuideLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonicalPath="/guides/aws-secrets-manager-pricing"
  lastUpdated="2026-01-22"
  faqs={[
    {
      q: "What typically drives Secrets Manager cost?",
      a: "API call volume (GetSecretValue) plus a baseline per secret-month. In many workloads, request volume dominates if secrets are fetched frequently.",
    },
    {
      q: "Why do costs spike in Kubernetes and serverless?",
      a: "Cold starts and pod churn can trigger many secret fetches. If each instance fetches multiple secrets, request volume scales quickly.",
    },
  ]}
>
  <p>
    Secrets Manager costs are usually a combination of <strong>secret-month</strong> charges plus <strong>API request</strong>{" "}
    charges. The main pitfall is request-driven spend from applications fetching secrets too often.
  </p>

  <h2>What to model</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Secrets count</strong>: how many secrets you store across accounts/environments
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>API calls/month</strong>: GetSecretValue, PutSecretValue, DescribeSecret, List*, etc.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Caller patterns</strong>: per-request fetch vs per-startup fetch
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>A fast estimate</h2>
  <p class="muted">
    Use <a href="/calculators/aws-secrets-manager-cost-calculator/">AWS Secrets Manager Cost Calculator</a> to model secret-months
    and API calls with your effective pricing.
  </p>

  <h2>Validation checklist</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Confirm whether apps fetch secrets per request or per startup (per request is usually expensive).</li>
    <li>Estimate calls/month from instance count and fetch frequency; then validate with a real week of metrics.</li>
    <li>Watch for spike drivers: pod churn, cold starts, and retry loops.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Related tools</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a class="btn" href="/calculators/aws-secrets-manager-cost-calculator/">Secrets Manager cost</a>
    <a class="btn" href="/guides/request-based-pricing/">Request-based pricing</a>
    <a class="btn" href="/guides/cloud-cost-estimation-checklist/">Cost checklist</a>
  </div>
</GuideLayout>
